hopobject.body: Could I have a statement, please? farmaciasocial.com.ar First-time buyer activity is viewed as a key bellwether of the wider market. The weakening or directionless trend of the market for much of the past five years has been blamed on lack of first-timer activity. That may now have changed, the data suggests. Since 2007 first-time buyers have accounted on average for 38c of house purchase loans. This latest quarterly data shows the figure to have risen to 46pc.
